    "arxiv": "[hep-ex/2504.06346v2](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2504.06346)",
    "time": "2025.04.08",
    "abstract": "An angular analysis of the decay $B_{s}^{0}\\to\\phi e^+e^-$ in three bins of dielectron mass squared $q^2$, using proton-proton collision data collected with the LHCb detector between 2011 and 2018 at centre-of-mass energies of 7, 8 and 13 TeV, corresponding to an integrated luminosity of 9 fb$^{-1}$. The observables $F_L$, $A'_6$, $S_3$ and $A_9$ are measured in the $q^2$ ranges [0.1, 1.1], [1.1, 6.0] and [15.0, 19.0] GeV$^2/c^4$. The results are compatible with Standard Model predictions.",
